    "contracts": {
      "confidence": "Exact one-sided Clopper-Pearson bounds for binary class recalls and exact positive-upper/negative-lower Clopper-Pearson bounds for paired {-1,0,1} target harm.",
      "envelope_multiplicity": "The reported post-selection shift envelope uses simultaneous Bonferroni coverage over every registered candidate-contract pair.",
      "leakage": "For every preregistered attacker, leakage is one half of the robust class-conditional recall for source class 0 plus one half of the robust class-conditional recall for source class 1. It is therefore invariant to source-class prior shift and equals 0.5 for a constant binary attacker.",
      "primary_multiplicity": "Each candidate is an intersection-union test: every component contract must reject violation at alpha delta/12. A union bound over the 12 registered candidates controls selection of any unsafe candidate. No multiplicity penalty across component contracts is required for the intersection-union test; each balanced-leakage component splits its candidate alpha across two class recalls.",
      "shift_model": "Target contracts permit arbitrary changes in environment mixture weights and bound the within-environment deployment-to-certification density ratio by Gamma. Balanced leakage fixes source-class weights at one half and separately bounds each within-source-class density ratio by Gamma. The guarantee applies to any external law satisfying these support and density-ratio assumptions; benchmark external results test, but do not prove, assumption membership.",
      "support_rule": "A declared deployment environment absent from certification, or a missing source class required by balanced leakage, makes the contract non-identifiable and forces VERA to abstain. Camelyon17 center 2 is the preregistered unsupported case and its external balanced leakage is reported as NA.",
      "target": "Maximum environment-conditional mean paired increase in zero-one target loss versus the identity edit."
    },
